2-4076-b58f-9aecb974819b_1536x1024.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>A few days ago, <strong><a href=\"https://open.substack.com/pub/drseantobin/p/the-rosary-gods-love-in-beads-and?r=5ltt2z&amp;utm_campaign=post&amp;utm_medium=web&amp;showWelcomeOnShare=false\">I posted about the Rosary</a></strong> — about its beauty, its biblical rhythm, and the way it forms the soul like breathing Scripture in motion.</p><p>Within hours, I started getting messages like this:</p><blockquote><p><em>“The Rosary is sorcery. Praying to Mary is necromancy. You’re contacting the dead. It’s forbidden in the Bible.”</em></p></blockquote><p>Another reel reaction even called the Pope’s coronation of the Child Jesus and Mary “idolatry.”</p><p>And I realized — this isn’t just disagreement. It’s a deep confusion about what worship actually is.</p><h3>🕊️ The Difference Between Worship and Honor</h3><p>Catholics do not worship Mary.<br>We honor her — just as Scripture itself commands:</p><p><em>“All generations will call me blessed.”</em> — Luke 1:48</p><p>To <strong>worship</strong> means to offer sacrifice to God alone.<br>To <strong>honor</strong> means to recognize someone’s participation in God’s grace.</p><p>The first belongs only to the Creator. The second belongs to the creatures who say “yes” to Him most fully.</p><p>When the Church crowns Mary, it’s not placing her above Christ — it’s recognizing her perfect re…</p>"}